narratives.question_text:
What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
(Your anonymous response to this question may be viewed by Yale College students, faculty, and advisers to aid in course selection and evaluating teaching.)
comments: You will learn about several dimensions of economic globalization in a way that incorporates both very technical economics materials and more policy-focused work. But there is absolutely no feedback on the quality of work, which is really difficult in terms of improvement
Feedback on our assignments and reading responses would be helpful.

comments: If you are not willing to proactively keep asking for feedback, you should take this course Credit/D or just keep in mind that your grade may not be what you expect.
Yes!!! Class with President Zedillo is a unique once-in-a-lifetime privilege. If you know what to ask, you can gain insights you could never find anywhere else.
